               <listBibl type="secondary">
                  <bibl><ptr target="bm:BerryEtAl2005EnAeGondar"/></bibl>
                  <bibl><ptr target="bm:Wubneh2003EnAeAbunBet"/></bibl>
               </listBibl>
               <note>
                  <ab type="description">Abun Bet is a quarter north-west of the castles in <placeName
                        ref="LOC3577Gondar">Gondar</placeName>. It was the residence of the
                     Metropolitan (<roleName type="title">abun</roleName>) and a place of asylum.
                     Its location changed over the centuries: it was first located near <placeName
                        ref="LOC6540Entone">Abba Ǝnṭonǝs</placeName> church; then, in the second
                     half of the <date>18th century</date>, it was moved near <placeName ref="LOC6539Gabrǝel"
                        >Gābrǝʾel</placeName> church; finally, during the Italian occupation, it was
                     briefly moved near <placeName ref="LOC6541DabraSahaySell">Dabra Śahay
                        Śǝllase</placeName> before the site near <placeName ref="LOC6539Gabrǝel"
                        >Gābrǝʾel</placeName> church was restored following the Italians' expulsion
                     in <date>1941</date>.</ab>
               </note>
            </place>
